// Bespoke sub-topic clusters, mentor hints, and correct-answer shortenings
// for the OpenSAT-imported question bank (~1,200 SAT prep questions spanning
// Reading & Writing and Math sections, each across Easy/Medium/Hard difficulty).
//
// OPEN_SAT_SUB_TOPICS groups each chapter's questions into 3-8 clusters that
// map directly onto official SAT domains (R&W: Information & Ideas, Craft &
// Structure, Expression of Ideas, Standard English Conventions; Math: Algebra,
// Advanced Math, Problem-Solving & Data Analysis, Geometry & Trigonometry),
// with sub-clusters surfacing the dominant question types in each domain.
//
// OPEN_SAT_MENTOR_HINTS overrides the generic OpenSAT scaffold hint with a
// one-line second-person nudge that names the testmaker's reasoning move
// without giving away the answer — voice: experienced SAT tutor pointing at
// the specific lever (plug-in, back-substitution, eliminate trap phrasing,
// label-the-figure, etc.) the question rewards.
//
// OPEN_SAT_CORRECT_SHORTENED trims correct strings flagged by the length-
// heuristic audit (correct >= 1.8x longer than longest wrong AND >= 20 chars
// longer). Trimmed explanatory clauses are reattached via lessonAddendum so
// no information is lost.

